# gen118 (rung 19 + L10) — bilingual ratchet for rule induction. The same
# code path (parse transitions -> fit a global or parity-split rule -> apply it)
# runs from an Italian query: the induction competence lives in the algorithm,
# not in an English phrasebook. Only the intent words differ (continua da, cosa
# viene dopo); the arrow notation, the fitting, and the rule report are shared.

# A held-out CONDITIONAL rule (even: n/2, odd: 2n+2) induced from four points,
# then run from 7 down to 1 — discovered, not told, in Italian.
> 4 -> 2, 8 -> 4, 3 -> 8, 5 -> 12. continua da 7.
< 7 -> 16 -> 8 -> 4 -> 2 -> 1. (induced if even: n / 2; if odd: 2n + 2.)

# A global multiplicative law (3n) induced, applied to a held-out 5.
> 10 -> 30, 4 -> 12, 7 -> 21. cosa viene dopo 5?
< 15. (rule: f(n) = 3n.)
